@startuml async-poll-record-lifecycle
' Lifecycle of the agentry-async-{requestId} ConfigMap, as seen by a poller.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/api/async-responses.md
!include _style.puml
skinparam wrapWidth 400

state "Absent" as Absent $mutedBg
state "Placeholder" as Placeholder
state "Patched" as Patched
state "Expired" as Expired $mutedBg

Absent : GET returns **404**
Placeholder : GET returns **202**\n+ backoff-aware Retry-After\n(2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, 30s, capped)
Patched : GET returns **200**\nwith the callback payload
Expired : GET returns **404**

[*] --> Absent

Absent --> Placeholder : placeholder **Create**, synchronously\nbefore the inbound 202 is returned\n(Create fails: caller sees 503, no requestId)

Placeholder --> Patched : payload **Patch**\n(agent response, or an error envelope)

Placeholder -[#B71C1C]-> Expired : **silent loss**\nnow - creationTimestamp > 1h
Patched --> Expired : now - creationTimestamp > 1h

Expired -up-> Absent : reconciler prune\n(expires-at annotation, live channels only)

note bottom of Absent
  **Channel deletion is the other way back to Absent,**
  and it is not expiry-gated: the AgentChannel finalizer
  sweeps every agentry-async-* record for that channel by
  label selector, whatever state it is in. A Placeholder or
  Patched record still inside its 1h TTL goes too.
end note

note right of Expired
  **Read-side, not the pruner.** The 404 is
  computed on every poll from the placeholder's
  creationTimestamp. The ConfigMap may still sit
  in etcd; pruning is storage cleanup only, and
  never what a poller observes.
end note

note left of Absent
  TTL clock starts at the placeholder
  **Create** (202-acceptance) and is
  **not** reset by the Patch, so the
  window is 1h regardless of how long
  the agent takes to reply.
end note

legend bottom
  **The red edge is the silent-loss edge (v1).** A record that never gets its Patch
  simply ages out. Both documented v1 limitations reach Expired along this **same** edge:
  **Replica Failure** (the replica holding the in-memory delivery pipeline dies after the
  202) and **Response-Patch Failure** (all 4 Patch attempts fail, raising
  agentry_channel_async_patch_failed_total). Either way **no envelope is ever stored**:
  pollers see 202 until the TTL flips them to 404, which is why callers should treat an
  unanswered poll past 5 to 10 minutes as failed and resubmit for a fresh requestId.
endlegend
@enduml
